{
  "stem": "4967.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the German made a speech through-- through a loudspeaker that this bloody, dirty Jew has been hanged because he shot a German officer.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you people don't think you can start nonsense with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Anybody who tries anything of nonsense, not only one will be shot, but hundred for one.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If you're going to kill one German, we'll kill 100 Jewish people on the spot here.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And apparently, this guy was a partisan, and he was caught.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If he killed a German or not, this is not to my knowledge.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Those things we don't speak.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And it was already 1943, beginning of '44.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And rumors came that the Russian were advancing on the front line.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we knew that General [NON-ENGLISH] is stuck not far from Stalingrad.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the Germans became very strict and very aggressive and very sadistic.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "People used to come back from work at the gate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They used-- we used to call it the-- the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Everybody used to come in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Some of them used to be searched in case they smuggled in a piece of bread, a potato, or whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My cousin, which is in Los Angeles, [INAUDIBLE]-- they used to call her the chicken woman.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She always used to smuggle in live chickens.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[CHUCKLES] And one day, it happened that one chicken made a loud noise.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "She let it run away, because the Germans, if they catch it on your body, a chicken or whatever it is, you don't stand a chance to be a survivor.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And people used to be scared to smuggle in things.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
